                aspect "Symmetric Key Protection"
                detail "Ensures that symmetric keys used for authentication are securely stored and
                    +b managed within hardware components designed to resist unauthorized access and
                    +b tampering."
            {
                aspect "Hardware Security Modules (HSMs)"
                detail "Encourages the use of dedicated hardware security modules to store and manage
                    +b symmetric keys securely, providing a hardware-based root of trust."
            {
                aspect "Tamper Resistance"
                detail "Hardware should be designed to resist physical tampering, which includes
                    +b mechanisms to detect and respond to attempts at unauthorized access."
            {
                aspect "Access Control"
                detail "Strict access control mechanisms must be in place to ensure that only
                    +b authorized processes can interact with the cryptographic keys."
